org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.languages.java.reverse.ui.handlers

Class AbstractExecuteInJobHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.core.commands.common.EventManager
      • org.eclipse.core.commands.AbstractHandler
        • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.languages.java.reverse.ui.handlers.AbstractExecuteInJobHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.commands.IHandler, org.eclipse.core.commands.IHandler2
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JavaCodeReverseInJobHandler

    public abstract class AbstractExecuteInJobHandler
extends org.eclipse.core.commands.AbstractHandler
    A base class to implemnet ui IHandler that should run in a Job and in a transactional command.
    This class must be subclassed, and the following method should be implemented :
    • #getJobName()
    • {@link #doPrepareExecute(ExecutionEvent)}
    • {@link #doExecuteTransactionInJob(IProgressMonitor)}
    This method are called in the previous order.
    This class also provides miscellaneous methods.
    Author:
    cedric dumoulin
